cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with session-based recommendation using Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and proposes two extensions for handling long-term dependencies and temporal aspects of user-item interactions. These are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, which suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely candidates as they cover topics related to recommendation systems and RNNs. Additionally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible categories as they cover topics related to sequence modeling and privacy-preserving recommendation systems, respectively.
